---
layout: post
title:  "Installing GCC 4.9.3 in Fedora 24"
date:   2016-08-31 21:45:07 +0900
categories: jekyll update
---

<h2>How to install in Fedora &gt;=24?</h2>

<p>1) su</p>

<p>2) rpm --import https://copr-be.cloud.fedoraproject.org/results/davidva/gcc49/pubkey.gpg</p>

<p>3) wget -P /etc/yum.repos.d/ https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kuboosoft/spec-testing/master/REPOSITORY/_copr_davidva-gcc49.repo</p>

<p>4) dnf install gcc49</p>

<h1>How to use?</h1>

<p>*You can change the environment variables as follows adding</p>

<p><code>source /usr/bin/gcc49</code></p>
<p><code>export PATH=/opt/gcc-4.9.3/bin:$PATH</code></p>

<h1>Set path to .so file</h1>

<p>sudo ln -s /opt/gcc-4.9.3/lib64/gcc/x86_64-fedoraunited-linux-gnu/lib64/libgcc_s.so /usr/lib64/libgcc_s.so</p>

<h2>DONE!</h2>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

